Thorax.
–

Scutum black with dark red-brown below lateral postsutural vitta, around mesonotal suture, between postpronotal lobe and notopleuron, inside postpronotal lobe. Pleural area fuscous to black except red-brown below postpronotal lobe. Yellow markings as follows: postpronotal lobe; notopleuron; mesopleural stripe reaching to anterior 
